      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Build apps, libraries, frameworks, plug-ins, and other executable code that run natively",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "on Apple silicon. When you build executables on top of Apple frameworks and technologies,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the only significant step you might need to take is to recompile your code for the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "arm64",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " architecture. If you rely on hardware-specific details or make assumptions",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "about low-level features, modify your code as needed to support Apple silicon.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "apple-silicon-1.png",
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Getting the best performance on Apple silicon sometimes requires making adjustments",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to the way you use hardware resources. Minimize your dependence on the hardware by",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "using higher-level technologies whenever possible. For example, use Grand Central",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Dispatch instead of creating and managing threads yourself. Test your changes on",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Apple silicon to verify that your code behaves optimally.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
